# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: BlackMonolith | Scene: TheBlackMonolithMage12
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Late at night, Sarah returned to her desk."
    new "Late at night, Sarah returned to her desk."

    old "The letter sat where it had been left behind."
    new "The letter sat where it had been left behind."

    old "She had not been able to put off opening it much longer."
    new "She had not been able to put off opening it much longer."

    old "Her hand trembled as she fished it off the table."
    new "Her hand trembled as she fished it off the table."

    old "She held it in her hands as if even a slight touch could ruin it."
    new "She held it in her hands as if even a slight touch could ruin it."

    old "Sarah gathered her strength and then finally ripped open the letter."
    new "Sarah gathered her strength and then finally ripped open the letter."

    old "As expected, there were only a few pages inside, nothing more."
    new "As expected, there were only a few pages inside, nothing more."

    old "Scrawled out across the surface, Metis' handwriting."
    new "Scrawled out across the surface, Metis' handwriting."

    old "Sarah began to read."
    new "Sarah began to read."

    old "Dear Xan, I write you this letter because I fear that our paths did not cross."
    new "Dear Xan, I write you this letter because I fear that our paths did not cross."

    old "When you are reading this, I will already be well on my way towards the Isles of Karpath."
    new "When you are reading this, I will already be well on my way towards the Isles of Karpath."

    old "I still remember the days we had spend on that beach, the ruins."
    new "I still remember the days we had spend on that beach, the ruins."

    old "You were guarded of me back then, but I must return there now."
    new "You were guarded of me back then, but I must return there now."

    old "Not merely for the memories."
    new "Not merely for the memories."

    old "I wish that I could speak more to you, but I find these days that most everyone in the Order has become a gossip."
    new "I wish that I could speak more to you, but I find these days that most everyone in the Order has become a gossip."

    old "Perhaps they were always like that."
    new "Perhaps they were always like that."

    old "Regardless, I can speak more on the matter when we meet. Truly meet."
    new "Regardless, I can speak more on the matter when we meet. Truly meet."

    old "The reason for leaving you this letter however, has nothing to do with my travel plans."
    new "The reason for leaving you this letter however, has nothing to do with my travel plans."

    old "Rather, there is a matter that I had been hoping to look into further, but I find myself struggling for time."
    new "Rather, there is a matter that I had been hoping to look into further, but I find myself struggling for time."

    old "Included with this letter you will find a report submitted by an acolyte from the Order."
    new "Included with this letter you will find a report submitted by an acolyte from the Order."

    old "She analyzed magical paterns from one of our measuring stations deep in the Mythran heartland."
    new "She analyzed magical paterns from one of our measuring stations deep in the Mythran heartland."

    old "It describes an anomaly, produced by rhythmic magical pulses, eminating from the further North."
    new "It describes an anomaly, produced by rhythmic magical pulses, eminating from the further North."

    old "This station lies close to the Mythran border with the jungles of Nephatim."
    new "This station lies close to the Mythran border with the jungles of Nephatim."

    old "As you are well aware, more than most even, this leaves few real potential sources for the origin of this signal."
    new "As you are well aware, more than most even, this leaves few real potential sources for the origin of this signal."

    old "Varany. The oldest city."
    new "Varany. The oldest city."

    old "The Order has left the city to its ruins, and rightly so. For millenia it was silent."
    new "The Order has left the city to its ruins, and rightly so. For millenia it was silent."

    old "But you have perhaps infected me with your paranoia, and I cannot help but wonder...what if."
    new "But you have perhaps infected me with your paranoia, and I cannot help but wonder...what if."

    old "Our Order holds a near singular grip on magic in the world."
    new "Our Order holds a near singular grip on magic in the world."

    old "The jungle Tribes have shown no aptitude or interest in it."
    new "The jungle Tribes have shown no aptitude or interest in it."

    old "I fear I have no more of an answer to that question than you likely do."
    new "I fear I have no more of an answer to that question than you likely do."

    old "However, you do possess a singular advantage. The House."
    new "However, you do possess a singular advantage. The House."

    old "It was my intention to discuss with you an expedition to Varany, even though I am well aware of your position."
    new "It was my intention to discuss with you an expedition to Varany, even though I am well aware of your position."

    old "For the time being, I would ask that you consider the matter."
    new "For the time being, I would ask that you consider the matter."

    old "When next we meet, I hope we can continue this discussion."
    new "When next we meet, I hope we can continue this discussion."

    old "I look forward to your opinion on the matter, as always."
    new "I look forward to your opinion on the matter, as always."

    old "Your loyal student and more, Metis."
    new "Your loyal student and more, Metis."

    old "Sarah placed the letter back down on the desk."
    new "Sarah placed the letter back down on the desk."

    old "She tried processing its contents."
    new "She tried processing its contents."

    old "Even now, she had no idea what to make of Metis...was this all trap? Had he left her the letter on purpose, knowing her curiosity would get to her?"
    new "Even now, she had no idea what to make of Metis...was this all trap? Had he left her the letter on purpose, knowing her curiosity would get to her?"

    old "No, thought Sarah."
    new "No, thought Sarah."

    old "He was a poweful mage in his own right. If he suspected anything, why would he have need of tricks?"
    new "He was a poweful mage in his own right. If he suspected anything, why would he have need of tricks?"

    old "So what then..."
    new "So what then..."

    old "She kept turning the letter about in her hand."
    new "She kept turning the letter about in her hand."

    old "Varany. The oldest city. The first city of Men, before the world had collapsed by the incursion of the world beyond."
    new "Varany. The oldest city. The first city of Men, before the world had collapsed by the incursion of the world beyond."

    old "Where the Empress had forged two worlds into one..."
    new "Where the Empress had forged two worlds into one..."

    old "Xan had told her stories from that place. And if she could believe it, he had even walked that city at its peak."
    new "Xan had told her stories from that place. And if she could believe it, he had even walked that city at its peak."

    old "And now the mysterious letter, speaking of unexplained phenomena..."
    new "And now the mysterious letter, speaking of unexplained phenomena..."

    old "Sarah knew what she had to, despite the danger of it."
    new "Sarah knew what she had to, despite the danger of it."

    old "Metis' arrival had reminded her of one fact. The world, even if she might ignore it, would still be out there."
    new "Metis' arrival had reminded her of one fact. The world, even if she might ignore it, would still be out there."

    old "She could not hide away in this place forever."
    new "She could not hide away in this place forever."

    old "Sarah began to pack swiftly, but in truth, she travelled light."
    new "Sarah began to pack swiftly, but in truth, she travelled light."

    old "In only a few hours, she stood ready to depart."
    new "In only a few hours, she stood ready to depart."

    old "Samayra came to see her off."
    new "Samayra came to see her off."

    old "So...I guess you're leaving again."
    new "So...I guess you're leaving again."

    old "I'll...miss you."
    new "I'll...miss you."

    old "Well...I don't know when you'll be back."
    new "Well...I don't know when you'll be back."

    old "You're coming with me, aren't you?"
    new "You're coming with me, aren't you?"

    old "Sarah saw Samayra's face go wide."
    new "Sarah saw Samayra's face go wide."

    old "Then the girl leapt forward and hugged her."
    new "Then the girl leapt forward and hugged her."

    old "Sarah! Really! Can I come?"
    new "Sarah! Really! Can I come?"

    old "Sarah laughed as she tried to hold Samayra off."
    new "Sarah laughed as she tried to hold Samayra off."

    old "Well, I mean...you know some magic right?"
    new "Well, I mean...you know some magic right?"

    old "I can use all the help that I can."
    new "I can use all the help that I can."

    old "Ooh! Sarah, I promise I won't be a burden, I promise!"
    new "Ooh! Sarah, I promise I won't be a burden, I promise!"

    old "Sarah smiled as she handed Samayra a bag of her own."
    new "Sarah smiled as she handed Samayra a bag of her own."

    old "In her heart, she worried."
    new "In her heart, she worried."

    old "Was the girl really ready for this? It would be safer to keep her here..."
    new "Was the girl really ready for this? It would be safer to keep her here..."

    old "But Sarah knew that this was impossible."
    new "But Sarah knew that this was impossible."

    old "She could not keep Samayra locked up in this house forever."
    new "She could not keep Samayra locked up in this house forever."

    old "And even when she had kept her here, Metis had made his way into the house."
    new "And even when she had kept her here, Metis had made his way into the house."

    old "The truth was that Samayra was only truly safe besides Sarah."
    new "The truth was that Samayra was only truly safe besides Sarah."

    old "Well...I'll be strict on you! Just as my teacher was!"
    new "Well...I'll be strict on you! Just as my teacher was!"

    old "Samayra nodded, smiling."
    new "Samayra nodded, smiling."

    old "And I'll be strong...just like you are!"
    new "And I'll be strong...just like you are!"

    old "Okay, well, rule number one, don't be a kiss-ass."
    new "Okay, well, rule number one, don't be a kiss-ass."

    old "Samayra stuck out her tongue as she flung the bag across her back."
    new "Samayra stuck out her tongue as she flung the bag across her back."

    old "Sarah saw that they were ready."
    new "Sarah saw that they were ready."

    old "She had the benefit of the House."
    new "She had the benefit of the House."

    old "I require a portal to Varany!"
    new "I require a portal to Varany!"

    old "Sarah declared it as loudly and as firmly as she could."
    new "Sarah declared it as loudly and as firmly as she could."

    old "Then she pulled upon a door."
    new "Then she pulled upon a door."

    old "Before them, the swirling magical energies revealed the jungles of the Oldest City."
    new "Before them, the swirling magical energies revealed the jungles of the Oldest City."

    old "With trembling hands, Sarah forced herself to be brave."
    new "With trembling hands, Sarah forced herself to be brave."

    old "Then she felt Samayra's hand on hers."
    new "Then she felt Samayra's hand on hers."

    old "She looked into the smiling face of the girl, and her heart steadied."
    new "She looked into the smiling face of the girl, and her heart steadied."

    old "Together."
    new "Together."

    old "They each took one step and crossed a million."
    new "They each took one step and crossed a million."

    old "Before her, the swirling magical energies revealed the jungles of the Oldest City."
    new "Before her, the swirling magical energies revealed the jungles of the Oldest City."

    old "She took one step and crossed a million."
    new "She took one step and crossed a million."

